alert.note: Alert for Central Aleutians (Alaska) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 14 at 11:48AM AKST until November 15 at 5:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 AM AKST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...West to Southwest winds 45 to 60 mph with gusts up to 80 mph expected. * WHERE...Central Aleutians, including Adak and Atka. * WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to 5 AM AKST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property, and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds will peak in Adak around Midnight tonight and in Atka around 3 AM Wednesday.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind. Prepare for the possibility of widespread power outages. Use caution if you must drive.
